\mathcal{X}
\mathcal{N}
\sigma_{\mathcal{X}}^2
\sigma_{\mathcal{N}}^2
 \rho_{XY} = E\left[\frac{X-E[X]}{\sigma_{\mathcal{X}}}\frac{Y-E[Y]}{\sigma_{\mathcal{N}}}\right] 
E
\mathcal{X}
\mathcal{N}
X, N
Y=X+N
Cov(X,Y)=Cov(X,X+N)=Cov(X,X)+Cov(X,N)=Var(X)+0=σ_X^2
Var(Y)=Var(X+N)=Var(X)+Var(N)+2Cov(X,N)=σ_X^2+σ_N^2+0
ρ_{X,Y}=\frac{Cov(X,Y)} {\sqrt{Var(X)Var(Y)}}=\frac{σ_X^2}{\sqrt{σ_X^2(σ_X^2+σ_N^2)}}=\frac{σ_X}{\sqrt{σ_X^2+σ_N^2}}=\frac{1}{\sqrt{1+\frac{σ_N^2}{σ_X^2}}}
